<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?><?Xpress productLine="ncc-clause" ?><clause xmlns:xt="urn:xpressauthor:trackchanges" id="_3cac54d5-ee2b-4ca8-98ff-08915fdc03d0" outputclass="ncc-clause"><meta><facet building="Class 2"/><facet building="Class 3"/><facet building="Class 4"/><facet building="Class 5"/><facet building="Class 6"/><facet building="Class 7a"/><facet building="Class 7b"/><facet building="Class 8"/><facet building="Class 9a"/><facet building="Class 9b"/><facet building="Class 9c"/><facet building="Class 10b"/></meta><sptc>10.2.31</sptc><title id="_6bf7cac6-427f-4137-a324-28bf08e3f1af">Door jambs on tiled floors</title><archive-num>New for 2022</archive-num><subclause id="_08675a8d-a0d4-4d9b-84c4-5905d7d2bbd5" outputclass="subclause"><title id="_bcadb625-894a-4fdd-bf75-0d9f30804d8e">SubClause</title><num>1</num><p>Where the bottom of a door jamb does not finish above the floor tiling, the portion of the door frame below the floor tiling must be waterproofed to provide a continuous seal between the perimeter <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/1305_0.16.0.xml#_f3cdd6b2-0801-4750-ac8b-515dde29def5" id="_be341400-6340-4f83-a0fd-9e8d16a8bf77" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">flashing</xref> and the <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/4735_0.5.0.xml#_2fb1baed-5210-4b6f-a0d1-49efc309b967" id="_6c2fa9b8-daa5-433d-9085-b60fd01b6605" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">waterstop</xref>.</p></subclause></clause>